      <p>KIT Federal Credit Union (&quot;KIT&quot;) is a member-owned, not-for-profit
          financial institution that exists to provide superior financial products
          to our member-owners and their families. KIT was chartered in 1965 with
          the field of membership of the employees of A&amp;P grocery stores located
          in Kentucky, Indiana, and Tennessee. We began in a one-room office and
          slowly built our services over the years by commitment of the official
          family to the members. In response to our growth and after several location
          changes in offices, we moved to our present location on Bardstown Road
          in Central Jefferson County just off the main expressway.<br />
       <br />
        With the new expanded area, we were then able to add services needed
        by the membership to properly manage their affairs. KIT geared up
        for the electronic age and added certificate, IRA, share draft (with
        ATM cards), home equity, and full revolving credit programs.<br />
       <br />
        In the early 1980's, a realization that the economic environment
        for the grocery industry was changing prompted the Board and CEO
        to prepare for a different future. A new strategy was built to stabilize
        the membership by adding Select Employee Groups as additional Sponsors.
        The management team took this and other positive steps to make sure
        the current members would not be left behind while adding new groups.
        In 1982, the announcement came that all A&amp;P stores would close.
        We then offered the membership to the Kentucky Grocers Association
        and sought other Sponsors whose workers were in need of a strong
        financial institution that cared about the people they served.<br />
       <br />
        Since then the <%= link_to "Sponsor list", loac_path %> has grown to other associations and like groups. In 2004,
        the KIAWA Credit Union merged with KIT and the Kentucky/Indiana Automotive
        Warehouse Association and KIT welcome the Association and its members
        as new sponsors. Here, a member is not a number; a member is an owner
        who has entrusted us with their financial needs. Adding groups was
        not our only focus - we added new services, too! Money market accounts,
        credit cards, an expanded non-purchase real estate program, first
        mortgages (through a third party servicer), and debit cards were
        added.<br />
       <br />
        Efficient and friendly service at all times is our goal and our pledge
        to our members. This is a trust we take seriously and hope you will
        join us today.</p>
        
